snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a teacher of literature and I taught this song (translated in English) as a sample text for identifying literary devices, tone, and imagery. I got obsessed with the song last year and tried to use it in my teaching, too (a typical teacher's behaviour, I know 😂).

I had no idea how it would strike the students of the first semester. Nor did I know how they would react to a translated song. It was a showstopper, tbh! 

Thanks for making this song.

snippet.textDisplay: 3:17 December 2024… the month I learned what first love feels like and what heartbreak tastes like. I’d walk into school just to steal a glance at her, wait in the cold for hours just to feel seen. Evenings were colder; I’d come home, drop my bag, fall on my bed, and play this song on repeat. At 3:17, it felt like the music was tearing me apart, whispering the truth I couldn’t escape she was my first love, but she never felt the same.
